    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.21-22_0001a" />
             
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        5835 Vine St.
                        Lincoln, Neb.
                        4-11-1973
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I can't see much of what I am writing, but I want to get in touch with you a again somehow.</p>
                
                <p>I have just returned from Columbia, where I spent <del><unclear>6</unclear></del> six weeks reciting my stuff for the United Artists for record. The first album should be on
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.21-22_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    the market by June 1st, I understand. We recorded a<del/> mess of stuff, and it nearly did me up, I am still slacking much of the time.</p>
                
                <p>I <hi rend="double underline">do</hi> want to hear from you. There must be some news; What of the Biography and the <hi rend="caps">U.</hi> of Mo. Press? The book should have a real publisher;
                    
                    <note type="authorial">(See 3)</note>    
                    
                    <note type="authorial">Big things are brewing!!</note>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.21-22_0002a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial"><unclear>-3</unclear>-</fw>
                    
                    It's a fine thing.</p>
                
                <p>We have a new contract a for Black Elk movie, which may workout<sic>work out</sic> by July 31st. There are several bidders for rights &#8212; one recent one is for <unclear><hi rend="underline">movie</hi> a <hi rend="underline">commercial</hi></unclear> play. The <unclear>popper</unclear> came to see me at Columbia.
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.21-22_0002b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>
                    
                    I'm trying to get started again on <unclear>in of</unclear> second volume. Reviews have <hi rend="double underline">all</hi> been happy. It's not an autobiography so much as another Neihardt book, Hilda <unclear>says</unclear>.</p>
                
                <p>Do write me and tell about yourself and Bower.</p>
                
                <p>Does Bower know General Crook's short speech on Indian treaties?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Endless love.</salute> <signed>Gaki.</signed>
                </closer>
                    
                <note type="authorial">The Bancroft Memorial is listed as a "National Historic Site"!!!</note>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
